[1] Brazil (Mato Grosso)
Date: Thu 26 Mar 2009
Source: 24 Horas News [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.24horasnews.com.br/index.php?mat=285961>


Mato Grosso this year [2009] recorded 139 cases of serious dengue
[disease]. Of this total, 55 were confirmed, 84 are under
investigation, 133 are recovered, and 6 cases resulted in death. The
data of the 4th week of March [2009] were disclosed this Wednesday
[25 Mar 2009] by the State Secretariat of Health and announced in the
Dengue Epidemiological Bulletin. Despite the fall in number of
notifications, the alert for occurrence of cases of serious disease,
which have increased in recent months, continues.

There are 3928 reports of dengue fever for January-24 March [2009].
Compared with the same period of 2008 (5563 notifications), the
decline is 29 percent. According to Epidemiological Monitoring, all
141 municipalities in the state are directed to implement the actions
recommended by the state dengue contingency plan regarding reporting,
pesticide control, training and social mobilization.

In the state capital Cuiaba, the figures for cases of severe dengue
are as follows: 50 cases reported, 35 under investigation, 15
verified [cases], 48 progressed to recovery and 2 resulting in death.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

