[2] Brazil (Rondonia)
Data: Tue 24 Mar 2009
Source: G1 [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Brasil/0,,MUL1056589-5598,00-GARIMPEIRO+MORRE+COM+SUSPEITA+DE+DENGUE+HEMORRAGICA+EM+RONDONIA.html>


In Ariquemes in the 1st 2 months of this year [2009], 284 suspected
dengue disease cases were registered. In the 1st 6 weeks of the year,
1305 cases were recorded in Rondonia. The city also installed a
clinic for the treatment of patients with dengue. This measure
reduces the hospital capacity in the city.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmailorg>

******
[3] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Tue 24 Mar 2009
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/pais/cidades/mat/2009/03/24/dengue-mata-um-cada-tres-dias-na-bahia-754965503.asp>


Dengue in Bahia has reached alarming proportions. On average, there
are 2400 reports [of dengue cases] per week and one death every 3
days. Centers for hydration to attend to patients are already
operating in the capital and in the state. But the threat remains
[for dengue virus transmission] in the streets, with trash scattered
by those who have not yet become aware of the danger of dengue.

In the city of Itabuna, which has the largest number of confirmed
deaths, the hydration posts are working in hospitals since Saturday
[21 Mar 2009], with the help of military physicians. In the Bahia
capital, the 2 centers of hydration for the state will be initiated
tomorrow [25 Mar 2009]. The municipality's [hydration centers] are
already working.

According to the report released today [24 Mar 2009] by the State
Secretariat of Health, 26 597 cases of dengue were reported in Bahia
up to the 2nd week of March [2009], an increase of 291 percent over
the same period last year [2008]. 28 persons died due to this disease.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

[This is a "chronicle of an epidemic foretold." I have written that,
with time, the epidemics of dengue in Brazil would kill more and more
people, and this is nothing new. - Mod.LJS]

