[5] Paraguay
Data: Fri 20 Mar 2009
Source: Estadao [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/internacional,paraguai-ja-registrou-630-casos-de-dengue-neste-ano,342205,0.htm>


Paraguay has recorded 630 cases of dengue this year [2009]. According
to the Minister of Public Health, Esperanza Martinez, since January
2009, there were 630 confirmed cases of dengue in Paraguay, and 700
more people may have contracted the disease.

Ivan Allende, Director of Health Surveillance, explained that
Paraguay is suffering "an epidemic of dengue of low intensity, but
must avoid further spread. The people need to eliminate the water
where the mosquito is breeding."

--
