[6] Viet Nam (Ho Chi Minh City)
Date: Sat 28 Mar 2009
Source: Vietnam Net Bridge [edited]
<http://english.vietnamnet.vn/Health/2009/03/838824/>


More than 2200 people have been affected by dengue fever in Ho Chi
Minh City since early this year [2009], an increase of 8 percent over
the same period last year. The Municipal Health Department reports
that as many as 90 percent of households in such districts as Binh
Thanh, 12, and 6 were found to have mosquitoes.

The Preventive Medicine Department under the Health Ministry held a
meeting on 27 Mar [2009] to launch a national project to prevent a
possible dengue fever epidemic, especially in southern provinces
during the monsoon season.

The project, worth more than VND 91 billion [USD 5.1 million] is
expected to reduce the infection and fatality rates by 10 percent
from the average level of the 2003-2007 period.

--
